        <marginalia hand="Italian">
            <language ident="LA">
                <position place="tail" book_orientation="0">
                    <marginalia_text>
                        Ne in populari quidem Republica, nimis oportuit esse popularem. Ned&ugrave;m id in / regno tolerabile. Novus error ducis Guisij in Gallia: aliorum alibi.
                    </marginalia_text>
                    <person name="Henry I, duke of Guise"/> <!--it's likely that Harvey talks about this member of the De Guise family-->
                    <location name="Gaul"/>
                </position>
            </language>
            <translation>It is not appropriate to be too popular, not even in a Republic of the people. It is even less acceptable in a kingdom. The recent mistake of the 
                Duke of Guise in France, of others elsewhere.
            </translation>
        </marginalia>
        
